verbs.description: dade (third-person singular simple present dades, present participle dading, simple past and past participle daded)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, intransitive) To walk unsteadily, like a child; to move slowly.
examples: No sooner taught to dade, but from their mother trip.

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To hold up by leading strings or by the hand, as a toddler.
examples: Little children when they learn to go / By painful mothers daded to and fro.
